methods.businessTimeElapsed:
Returns the amount of business time in nanoseconds that has elapsed on the given day by the specified time.

:param time: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) - time
:return: (long) business time in nanoseconds that has elapsed on the given day by the specified time
methods.getBusinessPeriods:
Gets the business periods for the day.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.calendar.BusinessPeriod[]) the BusinessPeriods for the day
methods.getEOBD:
Gets the end of the business day.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) end of the business day
methods.getEndOfBusinessDay:
Gets the end of the business day.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) end of the business day
methods.getLOBD:
Gets the length of the business day in nanoseconds. If the business day has multiple periods, only the time
 during the periods is counted.

:return: (long) length of the day in nanoseconds
methods.getLengthOfBusinessDay:
Gets the length of the business day in nanoseconds. If the business day has multiple periods, only the time
 during the periods is counted.

:return: (long) length of the day in nanoseconds
methods.getSOBD:
Gets the start of the business day.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) start of the business day
methods.getStartOfBusinessDay:
Gets the start of the business day.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) start of the business day
methods.isBusinessDay:
Is this day a business day?

:return: (boolean) true if it is a business day; false otherwise.
methods.isBusinessTime:
Determines if the specified time is a business time for the day.

:param time: (io.deephaven.time.DateTime) - time.
:return: (boolean) true if the time is a business time for the day; otherwise, false.
